Daily Temperature Anomalies: 1,194 anomalies on 2026-05-19, accounting for ~24% of total events (1,194/5,000).
Trend Implication: The single-day result confirms the high anomaly rate of temperature sensors. Long-term monitoring would reveal daily/seasonal temperature patterns and anomaly trends.
4. Partition Pruning Performance (Q4)
Result (q4_pruning_report.txt)
Without pruning: 0.3598 seconds
With pruning: 0.5031 seconds
Speedup factor: 0.72x (slowdown)
Analysis
Unexpected Slowdown: Partition pruning did not improve query performance (0.5031s > 0.3598s), with a 28% slowdown.
Root Causes:
Small Dataset: The total data volume is tiny (5,000 events), so pruning overhead (metadata scanning, partition filtering) outweighs the benefits of reduced data scanning.
Few Partitions: The curated zone has a small number of daily partitions, limiting pruning efficiency.
Spark Overhead: Pruning logic introduces additional predicate pushdown and partition metadata checks for small-scale data.
Scalability Note: Partition pruning will deliver significant performance gains for large-scale datasets (100k+ events) with multiple time/sensor partitions, as it reduces the amount of Parquet data scanned.
5. Overall Pipeline Performance & Conclusion
5.1 Pipeline Effectiveness
End-to-End Functionality: The pipeline successfully ingests, processes, stores, and analyzes sensor data, meeting all experimental requirements (anomaly detection, multi-zone storage, SQL analytics, API exposure).
Reliability: The 3-broker Kafka cluster (RF=3, ISR=2) ensures fault tolerance, and Spark checkpointing guarantees streaming job recovery.
5.2 Key Findings
Anomaly Hotspot: The 10th hour is the main anomaly period, requiring targeted maintenance.
Sensor Reliability: Humidity sensors are most stable; pressure/temperature sensors have high anomaly rates.
Partition Pruning Tradeoff: Ineffective for small datasets but critical for large-scale data.
5.3 Limitations & Improvements
Limitations: Small dataset size limits performance optimization validation; single-day data lacks long-term trend analysis.
Improvements:
Increase data volume (100k+ events) to verify partition pruning benefits.
Extend data collection to multiple days for trend analysis.
Optimize Spark parameters (e.g., executor memory) for small-scale streaming jobs.
